MAN - MANUAL PAGE

man (section topic) (command) # view section topics below eg. man 5 passwd
man -f passwd # display a one-line summary for each matching page
man -K passwd #   display titles also discriptions of all manual pages related to keyword
  

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
NAVIGATION IN MAN 
D - scroll forward one half-screen
U - scroll backward one half-screen 
G - go to the start of the man page
shift+G - go to the end of the man page
Q - exit man and return to command shell prompt
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
Common Sections of the Linux Manual
1 - user commands
Both executable and shell programs
2 - system calls
Kernel routines that are invoked from user space
3 - library functions
Provided by program libraries
4 - special files
Such as device files
5 - file formats
For many configuration files and structures
6 - games and screensaveers
Historical section for amusing programs
7 - conventions, standards and miscellaneous
Protocols and file systems
8 - system administration and privileged commands
Maintenance tasks
9 - linux kernel API
Internal kernel calls
